    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level for a Medium model risk, Medium decision consequence COU. The single shortcoming — Test conditions achieving Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3 — is accepted because the COU is explicitly bounded to the ASTM F1717 single-condition protocol and the two-laboratory replication provides sufficient confidence in test reproducibility. All three QoIs satisfy both the E/uval < 1.96 and < 10% percent-difference acceptance criteria. The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for the stated COU.",
